  displayName: Manananggal
  description: Traditionally identified as a distinct aswang type, the manananggal
    is known for separating its upper torso and taking flight after dark. Folkloric
    accounts often depict it as a nocturnal predator linked to rooftops, windows,
    and vulnerable households. Its legend carries themes of dual identity, where
    outward human form conceals a violent nature that emerges in darkness.
  firstEncounterText: You've encountered a Manananggal!
